## 5. JWT STRATEGY - PATCH WORK ISSUES

### 5.1 Dual Format Support (Lines 52-60)

#### Current Patch Work:
```typescript
// Validate that the userId is either a valid UUID or a numeric string
const isNumeric = /^\d+$/.test(userId);
const isUUID = validate(userId);

if (!isNumeric && !isUUID) {
  throw new Error('Invalid user ID format: Expected numeric or UUID');
}
```

#### Problem:
This exists because of an ID migration - some tokens have numeric `sub`, others have UUID `publicId`.

#### Root Fix - Migration Strategy:

**Step 1**: Update all JWT generation to use `publicId` consistently:
```typescript
// In jwt.strategy.ts
async validate(payload: any) {
  // Only accept UUID format after migration
  const userId = payload.sub || payload.userId;
  
  if (!validate(userId)) {
    throw new Error('Invalid token format');
  }
  
  // Find by publicId only
  const user = await this.usersService.findOneByPublicId(userId);
  if (!user) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('User not found');
  }
  
  return { userId: user.publicId, email: user.email, role: user.role };
}
```

**Step 2**: Add token version/expiration for old format

### 5.2 Loose Payload Validation

#### Current:
```typescript
async validate(payload: any) {
  // Any object is accepted
}
```

#### Root Fix:
```typescript
interface JwtPayload {
  sub: string;      // userId (publicId)
  email: string;
  role: string;
  iat: number;
  exp: number;
}

async validate(payload: JwtPayload) {
  // Validate required fields
  if (!payload.sub || !payload.email || !payload.role) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('Invalid token payload');
  }
  
  // Validate email format
  const emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
  if (!emailRegex.test(payload.email)) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('Invalid email in token');
  }
  
  // Validate role
  if (!Object.values(UserRole).includes(payload.role)) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('Invalid role in token');
  }
  
  // ... rest of validation
}
```

### 5.3 Missing User Existence Check

#### Current:
```typescript
return { userId, email: payload.email, role: payload.role };
```

#### Problem:
- Strategy returns user info without verifying user still exists
- Deleted/suspended users can still use tokens

#### Root Fix:
```typescript
async validate(payload: JwtPayload) {
  const user = await this.usersService.findOneByPublicId(payload.sub);
  
  if (!user) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('User not found');
  }
  
  if (user.isSuspended) {
    throw new UnauthorizedException('Account suspended');
  }
  
  // Return fresh data from database
  return { 
    userId: user.publicId, 
    email: user.email, 
    role: user.role 
  };
}
```

