## 6. ADDITIONAL SECURITY ISSUES

### 6.1 No Firebase UID Storage

#### Problem:
Firebase UID from decoded token is never stored. This prevents:
- Account linking across devices
- Debugging authentication issues
- Revoking specific Firebase sessions

#### Fix:
```typescript
// Add to User entity
@Column({ nullable: true })
firebaseUid: string;

@Index({ unique: true })
@Column({ nullable: true })
firebaseUid: string;
```

### 6.2 Debug Logging in Production

#### Current (jwt.strategy.ts:17-31):
```typescript
console.log(
  '🔍 DEBUG: JWT Strategy - Authorization header:',
  req.headers.authorization,
);
```

#### Security Risk:
- Authorization headers logged to console
- Could expose tokens in logs

#### Fix:
```typescript
// Use NestJS logger with conditional debug
@Injectable()
export class JwtStrategy extends PassportStrategy(Strategy) {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(JwtStrategy.name);
  
  async validate(payload: JwtPayload) {
    if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
      this.logger.debug('JWT payload:', payload);
    }
    // ...
  }
}
```

